```suggestion
private lemma final_of_final_costructuredArrowToOver_small (L : A  T) (R : B  T) [Final R]
```
and similar below and in the docstring.
I think the entire `calc` block needs to be indented by two spaces.
Is it correct that the universes for the objects all need to be equal? Seems strange given that you're using the other universes in the proof below.

May I interest you in the following questionable-but-perhaps-less-so-than-the-current-code code:
```suggestion
    have hsT (X) : sT.counitInv.app X =  _ := rfl
    exact NatIso.ofComponents (fun X => CostructuredArrow.isoMk (Iso.refl _) (by simp [F'', hsT]))
```

Inconsequential, just in case you didn't know: the following also works:
```suggestion
  have (b : AsSmall B) : (CostructuredArrow.toOver L' (R'.obj b)).Final := by
```

```suggestion
    calc colimit (L  G)  colimit <| grothendieckProj L  L  G :=
```

```suggestion
  convert Iso.isIso_hom i
```

```suggestion
/-- The version of `final_of_final_costructuredArrowToOver` on small categories used to prove the
```

```suggestion
private lemma final_of_final_costructuredArrowToOver_small (L : A  T) (R : B  T) [Final R]
```

```suggestion
theorem final_of_final_costructuredArrowToOver (L : A  T) (R : B  T) [Final R]
```
